[Source "Chessable.com"]
[Comment "700-opening-traps-by-bill-wall/course/5128, variation/195023"]

{This is one of the oldest openings with a lot of traps and transpositions. 
Until the middle of the 19th century, most chess authorities thought the best 
place for the Bishop was on c4, threatening the f7 square with a lot of 
attacking possibilities. Around 1840, this opening fell out of favor due to 
improvements in Black’s Defense. It still has its traps and played by a few 
modern Grandmasters such as John Nunn and Sergei Dolmatov.} 1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 *

